          <h4 class="first_p">Create a new game:&nbsp</h4><p class="first_p">Click new game on the main menu.</p>
          <h4>Choosing your role:&nbsp</h4><p>Choose between being the CodeMaker or the CodeBreaker</p>
          <h4>Choosing color:&nbsp</h4><p>To change color of guess or during code making, click on the circle to toggle each color. Click until you have the desired combination.</p>
          <h4>CodeMaker:&nbsp</h4><p>Choose a code that the computer will try to break</p>
          <h4>CodeBreaker:&nbsp</h4><p>Try to break the code generated by the computer.</p>
          <h4>Color:</h4><p>Red, blue, yellow, green, magenta and Cyan</p>
          <h4>Feedback is given this way:</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>A black pin mean a rightly colored pin, wrongly placed.</li>
            <li>A white pin mean a right1y colored pin, righly placed.</li>
            <li>Only on feedback is given per colored guess.</li>
            <li>To win the game guess the correct code in 12 turn or less.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <h2>Please choose:</h2>
        <div class="game_container">
          <input type="submit" name="newgame" value="NewGame">
          <input id="how_to" type="submit" name="how_to" value="How to play">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="footer">
        <h6 class="game">MasterMind</h6>
